{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The generated function signature matches the expected interface (parameter names, types, return type) specified in the description.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: signature correctness is produced by the model from natural language, and can vary across runs/prompts. A mocked generator can hide real mismatches. No full multi-step session is required, just one real model generation plus signature validation.","test_description":"Send a natural-language spec with strict signature requirements to the real model, compile/parse the generated code, and assert exact match on function name, parameter names/order/types, and return type.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The generated implementation passes all provided test cases on the first or a subsequent attempt.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP + LLM-DEP: this behavior spans generate -> test -> refine attempts, and correctness depends on the sequence plus model outputs at each step. Single-call or mocked tests miss real retry dynamics.","test_description":"Run the real service end-to-end on a task with provided tests, allowing retries; assert that either attempt 1 or a later attempt passes all tests and the service returns the passing implementation/attempt metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.25,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When tests fail, the refinement step includes the failure messages in the next LLM prompt so the model can learn from its mistakes.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is primarily prompt-construction wiring between test runner output and retry prompt builder. A pure unit test can miss formatting/truncation/escaping issues across module boundaries; real LLM behavior is not required to detect inclusion.","test_description":"Force a failing test run with known failure text, trigger one retry, capture the constructed second prompt, and assert the expected failure messages are present (including key assertion lines and error context).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The service stops after 3 failed attempts and returns a structured error with all three attempts and their test results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-HIDE: retry-limit enforcement and error aggregation are orchestration concerns across generator, executor, and result serializer. In-process mocks are acceptable if they still exercise real retry coordinator and result schema.","test_description":"Use a deterministic failing generation/test setup so all attempts fail; execute the service and assert exactly 3 attempts were made, no 4th call occurred, and the returned error payload contains per-attempt code/test-result records for attempts 1-3.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full loop — generate, test, refine, test again — produces a working implementation for a function that a single LLM call typically gets wrong.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP is explicit, and LLM-DEP is central: success depends on iterative correction behavior, not just one call. Mocked outputs can make this always pass and hide true failure rates.","test_description":"Pick a benchmark prompt where one-shot generation usually fails but iterative refinement can succeed; run the real multi-attempt loop and assert initial failure followed by later passing tests within the 3-attempt limit.","plan_consistent